### Instruction:
in javascript how do you save to and read back from localstorage

### Response:

To save data to local storage in JavaScript, you can use the `localStorage` object. Here's an example of how you might save a string value:
```
// Save a string value to local storage
localStorage.setItem("myString", "Hello World!");

// Check if the string is stored in local storage
if (localStorage.getItem("myString")) {
  // The string is stored in local storage
} else {
  // The string is not stored in local storage
}
```
To read data from local storage, you can use the `localStorage.getItem` method. Here's an example of how you might retrieve a string value:
```
// Retrieve a string value from local storage
var myString = localStorage.getItem("myString");

// Check if the string is stored in local storage
if (myString) {
  // The string is stored in local storage
} else {
  // The string is not stored in local storage
}
```
